{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;\red255\green0\blue128;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 Sometimes when you have records in a parent-child relationship, you want changes to the parent and child to both be rolled back together. At other times, you may want to commit the child changes even if the parent change was cancelled.\par
\par
In this example, you can make changes to the child phone records, using either \cf2 Nested Deferred\cf1  or \cf2 Deferred\cf1  transactions. \par
\par
 \par
}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 Using Nested transactions, the child records will be committed even if you Cancel from the parent.\par
}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 Using Deferred transactions, the child record changes will be lost if you cancel out of the parent.\par
}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;\red255\green0\blue128;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 This subtask is opened in \cf2 Nested Deferred \cf1 mode. Make some changes to these phone numbers, then press Cancel in the parent task.\par
\par
The changes to the parent will go away, but the changes in this task will still exist.\par
}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;\red255\green0\blue128;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 This subtask is opened in \cf2 Deferred \cf1 mode. Make some changes to these phone numbers, then press Cancel in the parent task.\par
\par
The changes to the parent will go away, and so will the changes you made here.\par
\par
